<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n01036a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01036a">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01036a"> 36(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> private divorce bill / promoted in Lords / for domiciled Irishmen</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">No law court in this country&mdash;or in any country &mdash;has any power, where the husband is a <mark>domiciled Irishman</mark>, to dissolve a marriage <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Accordingly, up to the present, the only method by which an Irishman could break the <i>vinculum matrimonii</i> was by obtaining a <mark>private Act of Parliament</mark> for the purpose <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> <mark>A divorce bill is always originated in the Lords</mark> <small> <a name="IT11nov22" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IT11nov22"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (11 November 1922) 7/4</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05113f" href="c05all.htm#c05113f">VI.C.05:113(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
